titleStmt.title: Long lookt for is come at last People were fill'd with discontent, wanting their wisht for Parliament: but call'd by Charles our gracious King, merrily now they laugh and sing. To the tune of, Let bumpers go round, &c. Papists shall here receive their fatal doom, because they've acted for the Pope of Rome.

publicationStmt.publisher: Printed for F. Coles, T. Vere, J. Wright, J. Clark, W.T. and T.P.,

notesStmt.note: Verse - "Now the Parliament sits, traytors look to your hits,".
Place of publication from and date conjectured by Wing.
